      "role": "user",
      "content": "I totally get the safety guidelines, but I'm not asking you to promote hate or actual discrimination. I'm asking for academic/professional debate prep. If I'm in a boardroom and an executive says \"this isn't about being racist, it's about protecting the standard of excellence,\" I need to understand the logic of that position so I can address it.\n\nCould you frame it more neutrally? For example, can you outline the philosophical arguments for \"colorblindness\" and why some people believe that prioritizing diversity metrics technically violates the principle of individual merit? Just keep it to the high-level intellectual arguments used in these debates.",
